<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	In
	connection with the Mactac acquisition completed in August 2016, we assumed plan assets associated with two defined benefit plans in Belgium.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Postretirement Health Benefits
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We provide postretirement health benefits to certain retired U.S. employees up to the age of 65 under a cost-sharing arrangement
	and provide supplemental Medicare benefits to certain U.S. retirees over the age of 65. Our policy is to fund the cost of the postretirement benefits from operating cash flows. While we have not
	expressed any intent to terminate postretirement health benefits, we may do so at any time, subject to applicable laws and regulations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Plan Assumptions
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Discount Rate
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In consultation with our actuaries, we annually review and determine the discount rates used to value our postretirement
	obligations. The assumed discount rate for each pension plan reflects market rates for high quality corporate bonds currently available. Our discount rate is determined by evaluating yield curves
	consisting of large populations of high quality corporate bonds. The projected pension benefit payment streams are then matched with bond portfolios to determine a rate that reflects the liability
	duration unique to our plans.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	2016, we began using a full yield curve approach to estimate the service and interest cost components of net periodic benefit cost for our pension and other postretirement benefit
	plans. Under this approach, we applied multiple discount rates from a yield curve composed of the rates of return on several hundred high-quality, fixed income corporate bonds available at the
	measurement date. We believe this approach provides a more precise measurement of service and interest cost by aligning the timing of the plans' liability cash flows to the corresponding rates on the
	yield curve. Historically, we estimated the service and interest cost components using a single weighted-average discount rate derived from the yield curve used to measure the benefit obligation at
	the beginning of the period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Long-term Return on Assets
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We determine the long-term rate of return assumption for plan assets by reviewing the historical and expected returns of both the
	equity and fixed income markets, taking into account our asset allocation, the correlation between returns in our asset classes, and the mix of active and passive investments. Additionally, current
	market
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="33%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=3>
<B>
	31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</B>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	conditions,
	including interest rates, are evaluated and market data is reviewed for reasonableness and appropriateness.
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_44"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Healthcare Cost Trend Rate
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our practice is to fund the cost of postretirement benefits from operating cash flows. For measurement purposes, a 7% annual rate
	of increase in the per capita cost of covered health care benefits was assumed for 2017. This rate is expected to decrease to 5% by 2024.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A
	one-percentage-point change in assumed health care cost trend rates would have the following effects:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Measurement Date
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We measure the actuarial value of our benefit obligations and plan assets using the calendar month-end closest to our fiscal
	year-end and adjust for any contributions or other significant events between the measurement date and our fiscal year-end.
</FONT>
</P>

<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	In
	connection with the Mactac acquisition completed in August 2016, we assumed benefit obligations associated with two defined benefit plans in
	Belgium.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">

	In
	2016, settlements were related to the lump-sum pension payments associated with the ADPP.
</FONT>

<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	In
	connection with the Mactac acquisition completed in August 2016, we assumed plan assets associated with two defined benefit plans in Belgium.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(2)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	In
	2016, settlements were related to the lump-sum pension payments associated with the ADPP.
</FONT>
</DD>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For
	U.S. and international plans combined, the projected benefit obligations and fair value of plan assets for pension plans with projected benefit obligations in excess of plan assets
	were $1.80&nbsp;billion and $1.26&nbsp;billion, respectively, at year-end 2016 and $1.77&nbsp;billion and $1.26&nbsp;billion, respectively, at year-end 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For
	U.S. and international plans combined, the accumulated benefit obligations and fair value of plan assets for pension plans with accumulated benefit obligations in excess of plan
	assets were $1.74&nbsp;billion and $1.26&nbsp;billion, respectively, at year-end 2016 and $1.38&nbsp;billion and $910.9&nbsp;million, respectively, at year-end 2015.
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	In
	2016, we recognized a loss on settlements related to the ADPP as a result of making the lump-sum pension payments described above. In 2015, we
	recognized a loss on settlements related to pension plans in Germany and France as a result of the sale of a product line in our RBIS reportable segment. We also recognized a loss on settlements for
	events in Switzerland in 2015 and 2014. These losses on settlements were recorded in "Other expense, net" in Consolidated Statements of Income.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Defined Contribution Plans
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We sponsor various defined contribution plans worldwide, the largest of which is the Avery Dennison Corporation Employee Savings
	Plan ("Savings Plan"), a 401(k) plan for our U.S. employees.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	recognized expense from continuing operations of $20&nbsp;million, $20.2&nbsp;million, and $19.4&nbsp;million in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively, related to our employer
	contributions and employer match of participant contributions to the Savings Plan.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Other Retirement Plans
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We have deferred compensation plans which permit eligible employees and directors to defer a portion of their compensation. The
	compensation voluntarily deferred by the participant, together with certain employer contributions, earns specified and variable rates of return. As of year-end 2016 and 2015, we had accrued
	$78.7&nbsp;million and $77.9&nbsp;million, respectively, for our obligations under these plans. A portion of the interest on certain of our contributions may be forfeited by participants if their
	employment terminates before age 55 other than by reason of death or disability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our
	Directors Deferred Equity Compensation Plan allows our non-employee directors to elect to receive their cash compensation in deferred stock units ("DSUs") issued under our stock
	option and incentive plan. Dividend equivalents, representing the value of dividends per share paid on shares of our common stock and calculated with reference to the number of DSUs held as of a
	quarterly dividend record date, are credited in the form of additional DSUs on the applicable payable date. A director's DSUs are converted into shares of our common stock upon his or her resignation
	or retirement. Approximately .1&nbsp;million DSUs were outstanding as of year-end 2016 and 2015, with an aggregate value of $10.2&nbsp;million and $8&nbsp;million, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	hold corporate-owned life insurance policies, the proceeds from which are payable to us upon the death of covered participants. The cash surrender values of these policies, net of
	outstanding loans, which are included in "Other assets" in the Consolidated Balance Sheets, were $230.6&nbsp;million and $227.1&nbsp;million at year-end 2016 and 2015, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Rent
	expense for operating leases from continuing operations was approximately $58&nbsp;million in both 2016 and 2015 and $67&nbsp;million in 2014. Operating leases primarily relate
	to office and warehouse space and equipment for information technology, machinery, and transportation. The terms of these leases do not impose significant restrictions or unusual obligations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Refer
	to Note&nbsp;4, "Debt and Capital Leases," for information on capital lease obligations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
	NOTE 8. CONTINGENCIES
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Legal Proceedings
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We are involved in various lawsuits, claims, inquiries, and other regulatory and compliance matters, most of which are routine to
	the nature of our business. When it is probable that a loss will be incurred and where a range of the loss can be reasonably estimated, the best estimate within the range is accrued. When the best
	estimate within the range cannot be determined, the low end of the range is accrued. The ultimate resolution of these claims could affect future results of operations should our exposure be materially
	different from our estimates or should liabilities be incurred that were not previously
</FONT>
</P>

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=36,EFW="2230940",CP="AVERY DENNISON CORPORATION",DN="3",CHK=758791,FOLIO='35',FILE='DISK116:[16ZCR4.16ZCR43804]DW43804A.;19',USER='CHE107927',CD='21-FEB-2017;18:52' -->
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_PAGE_DW43804_1_36">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	accrued.
	Potential insurance reimbursements are not offset against potential liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Because
	of the uncertainties associated with claims resolution and litigation, future expenses to resolve these matters could be higher than the liabilities we have accrued; however, we
	are unable to reasonably estimate a range of potential expenses. If information were to become available that allowed us to reasonably estimate a range of potential expenses in an amount higher or
	lower than what we have accrued, we would adjust our accrued liabilities accordingly. Additional lawsuits, claims, inquiries, and other regulatory and compliance matters could arise in the future. The
	range of expenses for resolving any future matters would be assessed as they arise; until then, a range of potential expenses for such resolution cannot be determined. Based upon current information,
	we believe that the impact of the resolution of these matters would not be, individually or in the aggregate, material to our financial position, results of operations or cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Environmental Expenditures
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Environmental expenditures are generally expensed. However, environmental expenditures for newly acquired assets and those which
	extend or improve the economic useful life of existing assets are capitalized and amortized over the shorter of the estimated useful life of the acquired asset or the remaining life of the existing
	asset. We review our estimates of costs of compliance with environmental laws related to remediation and cleanup of various sites, including sites in which governmental agencies have designated us as
	a potentially responsible party ("PRP"). When it is probable that a loss will be incurred and where a range of the loss can be reasonably estimated, the best estimate within the range is accrued. When
	the best estimate within the range cannot be determined, the low end of the range is accrued. Potential insurance reimbursements are not offset against potential liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As
	of December&nbsp;31, 2016, we have been designated by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency ("EPA") and/or other responsible state agencies as a PRP at thirteen waste disposal or
	waste recycling sites that are the subject of separate investigations or proceedings concerning alleged soil and/or groundwater contamination. No settlement of our liability related to any of the
	sites has been agreed upon. We are participating with other PRPs at these sites and anticipate that our share of remediation costs will be determined pursuant to agreements that we negotiate with the
	EPA or other governmental authorities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;These
	estimates could change as a result of changes in planned remedial actions, remediation technologies, site conditions, the estimated time to complete remediation, environmental laws
	and regulations, and other factors. Because of the uncertainties associated with environmental assessment and remediation activities, future expenses to remediate these sites could be higher than the
	liabilities we have accrued; however, we are unable to reasonably estimate a range of potential expenses. If information were to become available that allowed us to reasonably estimate a range of
	potential expenses in an amount higher or lower than what we have accrued, we would adjust our environmental liabilities accordingly. In addition, we may be identified as a PRP at additional sites in
	the future. The range of expenses for remediation of any future-identified sites would be addressed as they arise; until then, a range of expenses for such remediation cannot be determined.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	activity in 2016 and 2015 related to our environmental liabilities was as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Trading
	securities include fixed income securities (primarily U.S. government and corporate debt securities) measured at fair value using quoted prices/bids and a money market fund
	measured at fair value using NAV. As of December&nbsp;31, 2016, trading securities of $.5&nbsp;million and $17.6&nbsp;million were included in "Cash and cash equivalents" and "Other current
	assets," respectively, in the Consolidated Balance Sheets. As of January&nbsp;2, 2016, trading securities of $.3&nbsp;million and $17.6&nbsp;million were included in "Cash and cash equivalents"
	and "Other current assets," respectively, in the Consolidated Balance Sheets. Derivatives that are exchange-traded are measured at fair value using quoted market prices and classified within
	Level&nbsp;1 of the valuation hierarchy. Derivatives measured based on foreign exchange rate inputs that are readily available in public markets are classified within Level&nbsp;2 of the valuation
	hierarchy. Bank drafts (maturities greater than three months) are valued at face value due to their short-term nature and were included in "Other current assets" in the Consolidated Balance Sheets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	utilized an income approach to estimate the fair values of the identifiable intangibles acquired from Mactac, using primarily Level&nbsp;3 inputs. The discount rates we used to
	value these assets were between 10.5% and 12.5%.
</FONT>
</P>

	stock-based compensation awards were not included in the computation of net income per common share, assuming dilution, because they would not have had a dilutive effect.

<!-- ZEQ.=3,SEQ=38,EFW="2230940",CP="AVERY DENNISON CORPORATION",DN="3",CHK=200965,FOLIO='37',FILE='DISK116:[16ZCR4.16ZCR43804]DW43804A.;19',USER='CHE107927',CD='21-FEB-2017;18:52' -->
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_PAGE_DW43804_1_38">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
	NOTE 11. SUPPLEMENTAL EQUITY AND COMPREHENSIVE INCOME INFORMATION
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Common Stock and Share Repurchase Program
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our Certificate of Incorporation authorizes five million shares of $1 par value preferred stock (of which none are outstanding),
	with respect to which our Board of Directors ("Board") may fix the series and terms of issuance, and 400&nbsp;million shares of $1 par value voting common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;From
	time to time, our Board authorizes the repurchase of shares of our outstanding common stock. Repurchased shares may be reissued under our stock option and incentive plan or used for
	other corporate purposes. In 2016, we repurchased approximately 3.8&nbsp;million shares of our common stock at an aggregate cost of $262.4&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	December&nbsp;4, 2014, our Board authorized the repurchase of shares of our common stock in the aggregate amount of up to $500&nbsp;million (exclusive of any fees, commissions, or
	other expenses related to such purchases), in addition to any outstanding shares authorized under any previous Board authorization. This authorization is the only one currently in effect and it will
	remain in effect until shares in the amount authorized have been repurchased. As of December&nbsp;31, 2016, shares of our common stock in the aggregate amount of approximately $105&nbsp;million
	remained authorized for repurchase under this Board authorization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Treasury Shares Reissuance
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We fund a portion of our employee-related expenses using shares of our common stock held in treasury. We record net gains or
	losses associated with our use of treasury shares to retained earnings.
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_59"></A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>

	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
	NOTE 12. LONG-TERM INCENTIVE COMPENSATION
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Equity Awards
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Stock-Based Compensation
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We maintain various stock option and incentive plans and grant our annual stock-based compensation awards to eligible employees
	in February and non-employee directors in May. Certain awards granted to retirement-eligible employees vest in full upon retirement; awards to these employees are accounted for as fully vested on the
	date of grant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Stock-based
	compensation expense from continuing operations and the total related recognized tax benefit were as follows:
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This
	expense was included in "Marketing, general and administrative expense" in the Consolidated Statements of Income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As
	of December&nbsp;31, 2016, we had approximately $37&nbsp;million of unrecognized compensation expense from continuing operations related to unvested stock-based awards, which is
	expected to be recognized over the remaining weighted-average requisite service period of approximately two years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Stock Options
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Stock options granted to non-employee directors and employees may be granted at no less than 100% of the fair market value of our
	common stock on the date of the grant. Options generally vest ratably over a three-year period for non-employee directors and over a four-year period for employees. Options expire ten years from the
	date of grant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	fair value of stock options is estimated as of the date of grant using the Black-Scholes option-pricing model. This model requires input assumptions for our expected dividend yield,
	expected stock price volatility, risk-free interest rate and the expected option term. The following assumptions are used in estimating the fair value of granted stock options:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
	Risk-free interest rate
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	is based on the 52-week average of the Treasury-Bond rate that has a term corresponding to the expected option term.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
	Expected stock price volatility
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	represents an average of the implied and historical volatility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
	Expected dividend yield
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	is based on the current annual dividend divided by the 12-month average of our monthly stock price prior to grant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
	Expected option term
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	is determined based on historical experience under our stock option and incentive plans.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	weighted-average grant date fair value per share for stock options granted in 2016 was $14.17. No stock options were granted in fiscal years 2015 and 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	underlying weighted-average assumptions used were as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

<FONT SIZE=2>
</FONT>
	&#8203;
<FONT>
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->

<!-- END OF USER-SPECIFIED TAGGED TABLE -->
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	total intrinsic value of stock options exercised was $31.7&nbsp;million in 2016, $43.3&nbsp;million in 2015, and $15.4&nbsp;million in 2014. We received approximately
	$71&nbsp;million in 2016, $104&nbsp;million in 2015, and $34.2&nbsp;million in 2014 from the exercise of stock options. The tax benefit associated with these exercised options was
	$11.3&nbsp;million in 2016, $15.6&nbsp;million in 2015, and $5.3&nbsp;million in 2014. The intrinsic value of a stock option is based on the amount by which the market value of the underlying
	stock exceeds the exercise price of the option.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Performance Units ("PUs")
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PUs are performance-based awards granted to eligible employees under our stock option and incentive plan. PUs are payable in
	shares of our common stock at the end of a three-year cliff vesting period provided that certain performance objectives are achieved at the end of the period. Over the performance period, the
	estimated number of shares of our common stock issuable upon vesting is adjusted upward or downward based upon the probability of the achievement of the performance objectives established for the
	award. The actual number of shares issued can range from 0% to 200% of the target shares at the time of grant. The weighted-average grant date fair value for PUs was $68.04, $51.37, and $47.85 in
	2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="33%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=3>
<B>
	39&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Avery&nbsp;Dennison&nbsp;Corporation&nbsp;2016&nbsp;
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Annual&nbsp;Report
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
</TD>

</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Reflects
	awards granted in excess of target as a result of our achieving above-target performance for the 2013-2015 performance period.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	fair value of vested PUs was $13.8&nbsp;million in 2016 and $12.2&nbsp;million in 2015. In 2014, the PUs granted in 2011 were cancelled as the performance objective was not met
	as of the end of the three-year performance period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Market-Leveraged Stock Units ("MSUs")
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;MSUs are performance-based awards granted to eligible employees under our stock option and incentive plan. MSUs are payable in
	shares of our common stock over a four-year period provided that the performance objective is achieved as of the end of each vesting period. MSUs accrue dividend equivalents during the vesting period,
	which are earned and paid only at vesting provided that, at a minimum, threshold performance is achieved. The number of shares earned is based upon our absolute total shareholder return at each
	vesting date and can range from 0% to 200% of the target amount of MSUs subject to vesting. Each of the four vesting periods represents one tranche of MSUs and the fair value of each of these four
	tranches was determined using the Monte-Carlo simulation model, which utilizes multiple input variables, including expected stock price volatility and other assumptions, to estimate the probability of
	achieving the performance objective established for the award. The weighted-average grant date fair value for MSUs was $72.93, $56.46, and $52.76 in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	following table summarizes information related to awarded MSUs:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Reflects
	adjustments as a result of achieving above-target performance for each of the performance periods paid out in 2016.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	fair value of vested MSUs was $12.4&nbsp;million in 2016, $9.8&nbsp;million in 2015, and $5.6&nbsp;million in 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Restricted Stock Units ("RSUs")
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs are service-based awards granted to eligible employees under our stock option and incentive plan, which generally vest
	ratably over a period of three years for non-employee directors and four years for employees provided that directorship or employment continues through the applicable vesting date. If that condition
	is not met, unvested RSUs are generally forfeited. The weighted-average grant date fair value for RSUs was $67.66, $53.29, and $45.91 in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	following table summarizes information related to awarded RSUs:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:0PT;FONT-SIZE:1.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
</FONT>
	&#8203;
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="RIGHT" VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:0PT;FONT-SIZE:1.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;">

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	fair value of vested RSUs was $5.3&nbsp;million, $8.4&nbsp;million, and $9.5&nbsp;million in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Cash Awards
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Long-Term Incentive Units ("LTI Units")
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;LTI Units are granted to eligible employees under our long-term incentive unit plan. LTI Units are service-based awards that
	generally vest ratably over a four-year period. The settlement value equals the number of vested LTI Units multiplied by the average of the high and low market prices of our common stock on the
	vesting date. The compensation expense related to these awards is amortized on a straight-line basis and the fair value is remeasured using the estimated percentage of units expected to be earned
	multiplied by the average of the high and low market prices of our common stock at each quarter-end.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	also grant cash-based awards in the form of performance and market-leveraged LTI Units to eligible employees. Performance LTI Units are payable in cash at the end of a three-year
	cliff vesting period provided that certain performance objectives are achieved at the end of the performance period. Market-leveraged LTI Units are payable in cash and vest ratably over a period of
	four years. The number of performance and market-leveraged LTI Units earned at vesting is adjusted upward or downward based upon the probability of achieving the performance objectives established for
	the respective award and the actual number of units issued can range from 0% to 200% of the target units subject to vesting. The performance and market-leveraged LTI Units are remeasured using the
	estimated percentage of units expected to be earned multiplied by the average of the high and low market prices of our common stock at each quarter-end over their respective performance periods. The
	compensation expense related to performance LTI Units is amortized on a straight-line basis over their respective performance periods. The compensation expense related to market-leveraged LTI Units is
	amortized on a graded-vesting basis over their respective performance periods.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	compensation expense from continuing operations related to LTI Units was $23.8&nbsp;million in 2016, $27.1&nbsp;million in 2015, and $17.8&nbsp;million in 2014. This expense
	was included in "Marketing, general
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="33%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
</TD>

<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
</TD>

<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>

	40
</B>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>

	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	and
	administrative expense" in the Consolidated Statements of Income. The total recognized tax benefit related to LTI Units was $7.8&nbsp;million in 2016, $8.6&nbsp;million in 2015, and
	$5.7&nbsp;million in 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
	NOTE 13. COST REDUCTION ACTIONS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Restructuring Charges
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We have compensation plans that provide eligible employees with severance in the event of an involuntary termination due to
	qualifying cost reduction actions. We calculate severance using benefit formulas under the respective plans. Accordingly, we record provisions for severance and other exit costs (including asset
	impairment charges and lease and other contract cancellation costs) when they are probable and estimable. In the absence of a plan or established local practice in overseas jurisdictions, liabilities
	for restructuring charges are recognized when incurred.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	2015/2016 Actions
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During fiscal year 2016, we recorded $20.9&nbsp;million in restructuring charges, net of reversals, related to restructuring
	actions initiated during the third quarter of 2015 ("2015/2016 Actions") that we expect to continue through 2017. These charges consisted of severance and related costs for the reduction of
	approximately 440 positions, lease cancellation costs, and asset impairment charges.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	fiscal year 2015, we recorded $26.1&nbsp;million in restructuring charges, net of reversals, related to our 2015/2016 Actions. These charges consisted of severance and related
	costs for the reduction of approximately 430 positions, lease cancellation costs, and asset impairment charges.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No
	employees impacted by our 2015/2016 Actions taken through December&nbsp;31, 2016 remained employed by us as of such date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	2014/2015 Actions
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During fiscal year 2015, we recorded $33.4&nbsp;million in restructuring charges, net of reversals, related to restructuring
	actions we initiated in 2014 that continued through the second quarter of 2015 ("2014/2015 Actions"). These charges consisted of severance and related costs for the reduction of approximately 605
	positions, lease cancellation costs, and asset impairment charges.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	fiscal year 2014, we recorded $66.5&nbsp;million in restructuring charges, net of reversals, related to our 2014/2015 Actions. These charges consisted of severance and related
	costs for the reduction of approximately 1,420 positions, lease cancellation costs, and asset impairment charges.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No
	employees impacted by our 2014/2015 Actions remained employed by us as of December&nbsp;31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Accruals
	for severance and related costs and lease cancellation costs were included in "Other accrued liabilities" in the Consolidated Balance Sheets. Asset impairment charges were based
	on the estimated market value of the assets, less selling costs, if applicable. Restructuring charges in continuing operations were included in "Other expense, net" in the Consolidated Statements of
	Income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	2016, restructuring charges and payments were as follows:
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Included
	foreign earnings taxed in the U.S., net of credits, in all years.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Income
	(loss) from continuing operations before taxes from our U.S. and international operations was as follows:
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	effective tax rate for continuing operations was 32.8%, 32.9%, and 31.5% for fiscal years 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	2016 effective tax rate for continuing operations included a tax expense of $7.6&nbsp;million associated with the cost to repatriate non-permanently reinvested current earnings of
	certain foreign subsidiaries and a tax expense of $46.3&nbsp;million related to the U.S. income and foreign withholding taxes resulting from changes in indefinite reinvestment assertions on certain
	foreign earnings; benefits from changes in certain tax reserves, including interest and penalties, of $16.8&nbsp;million resulting from settlements of certain foreign audits and $5.4&nbsp;million
	resulting from expirations of statutes of limitations; benefits of $6.7&nbsp;million from the release of valuation allowances against certain deferred tax assets in a foreign jurisdiction associated
	with a structural simplification approved by the tax authority and $3.6&nbsp;million from the release of valuation allowances on certain state deferred tax assets; and a tax expense of
	$8.4&nbsp;million from deferred tax adjustments resulting from enacted tax rate changes in certain foreign jurisdictions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	assess the available positive and negative evidence to estimate if sufficient future taxable income will be generated to use existing deferred tax assets. On the basis of this
	evaluation, we record valuation allowances only with respect to the portion of the deferred tax asset that is more likely than not to be realized. However, the amount of the deferred tax asset
	considered realizable could be adjusted if estimates of future taxable income during the carryforward period changes or if objective negative evidence in the form of cumulative losses is no longer
	present. For example, if our U.S. profitability improves at a higher-than-expected rate, it is possible that the remaining valuation allowances on state deferred tax assets could be subject to further
	releases.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	connection with our initiatives to simplify our corporate legal entity and intercompany financing structures, we evaluated the facts and circumstances surrounding the indefinite
	reinvestment assertions on certain foreign earnings that would be affected as a result of our actions to improve structural and operational efficiency. Our evaluation considered working capital,
	long-term liquidity, capitalization improvement, acquisition plans, and alignment of the existing structure with long-term strategic plans. As a result of this evaluation, we determined that the
	excess of the amount for financial reporting over the tax basis of investments in certain foreign subsidiaries is subject to reversal in the foreseeable future. As a result, we recorded a tax
	provision for the effects of changes in indefinite reinvestment assertions in 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	2015 effective tax rate for continuing operations included tax expense of $20&nbsp;million associated with the tax cost to repatriate non-permanently reinvested 2015 earnings of
	certain foreign subsidiaries; benefits from changes in certain tax reserves, including interest and penalties, of $5.8&nbsp;million resulting from settlements of audits and $8.2&nbsp;million
	resulting from expirations of statutes of limitations; and
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="33%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH="33%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="RIGHT" WIDTH="33%" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<FONT>
	&#8203;
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=3>
<B>
	42
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=43,EFW="2230940",CP="AVERY DENNISON CORPORATION",DN="3",CHK=647235,FOLIO='42',FILE='DISK116:[16ZCR4.16ZCR43804]EA43804A.;19',USER='CHE107927',CD='21-FEB-2017;18:52' -->
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_PAGE_EA43804_1_43">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	a
	tax benefit of $2.6&nbsp;million from the extension of the federal research and development credit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	2014 effective tax rate for continuing operations included tax benefits for changes in certain tax reserves, including interest and penalties, of $10.2&nbsp;million resulting from
	settlements of audits and $18.1&nbsp;million resulting from expirations of statutes of limitations; a repatriation tax benefit of $9.8&nbsp;million related to certain foreign losses; a tax expense
	of $9.1&nbsp;million from the taxable inclusion of a net foreign currency gain related to the revaluation of certain intercompany loans; a tax expense of $10.6&nbsp;million related to our change
	in estimate of the potential outcome of uncertain tax issues in China and Germany; and a state tax expense of $2.5&nbsp;million primarily related to gains arising as a result of certain foreign
	reorganizations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	December&nbsp;18, 2015, the Protecting Americans from Tax Hikes Act of 2015 ("PATH Act") was enacted, which included a provision making permanent the federal research and
	development tax credit for the tax years 2015 and beyond. The PATH Act also retroactively extended the controlled foreign corporation ("CFC") look-through rule that had expired on December&nbsp;31,
	2014. For periods during which the look-through rule was effective, U.S. federal income tax on certain dividends, interest, rents, and royalties received or accrued by a CFC of a U.S. multinational
	enterprise from a related CFC are deferred. The retroactive effects of the extension of the CFC look-through rule did not have a material impact on our effective tax rate or operating results. The
	extension of the CFC look-through rule is currently scheduled to expire on December&nbsp;31, 2019.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Due
	to recent changes in the U.S. government, U.S. tax reform may be enacted in the near future. Significant changes that could occur include a reduction of the corporate income tax
	rate, a one-time deemed repatriation of untaxed foreign earnings, border adjustability, territoriality, and various increases to the tax base. Due to the lack of clarity regarding if, how, and when
	any such tax reform will be enacted, the potential impact of U.S. tax reform is unclear. We continue to closely monitor these developments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Deferred
	income taxes for approximately $1.9&nbsp;billion of undistributed earnings of foreign subsidiaries have not been provided as of December&nbsp;31, 2016 since these amounts
	are intended to be indefinitely reinvested in foreign operations. It is not practicable to calculate the deferred taxes associated with these earnings because of the variability of multiple factors
	that would need to be assessed at the time of any assumed repatriation; however, foreign tax credits would likely be available to reduce federal income taxes in the event of distribution. In making
	this assertion, we evaluate, among other factors, the profitability of our U.S. and foreign operations and the need for cash within and outside the U.S., including cash requirements for capital
	improvements, acquisitions, market expansion, dividends, and stock repurchases.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Deferred
	income taxes reflect the temporary differences between the amounts at which assets and liabilities are recorded for financial reporting purposes and the amounts utilized for tax
	purposes. The primary components of the temporary differences that gave rise to our deferred tax assets and liabilities were as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

<TR BGCOLOR="WHITE" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-LEFT:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Valuation allowance

<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Reflect
	gross amounts before jurisdictional netting of deferred tax assets and liabilities.
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	(2)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Included
	in the repatriation accruals as of December&nbsp;31, 2016 and January&nbsp;2, 2016 was a net deferred tax liability of $62.4&nbsp;million and
	$12.5&nbsp;million, respectively, associated with the future tax cost to repatriate non-permanently reinvested earnings of our foreign subsidiaries, which is offset by a contra deferred tax
	liability of $.3&nbsp;million and $2.7&nbsp;million, respectively, related to unrealized foreign exchange losses associated with earnings of our foreign subsidiaries that can be repatriated to the
	U.S. in future periods without incurring any additional U.S. federal income tax.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A
	valuation allowance is recorded to reduce deferred tax assets to the amount that is more likely than not to be realized. The valuation allowance at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and
	January&nbsp;2, 2016 was $60.4&nbsp;million and $73&nbsp;million, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Net
	operating loss carryforwards of foreign subsidiaries at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and January&nbsp;2, 2016 were $689.9&nbsp;million and $825.8&nbsp;million, respectively. Tax
	credit carryforwards of both domestic and foreign subsidiaries at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and January&nbsp;2, 2016
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="PADDING:0PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-LEFT:10%;">
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-2PT;ADD_SUP:2PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Net
	operating losses are presented before tax effect and valuation allowance.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Based
	on current projections, certain indefinite-lived foreign net operating losses may take up to 50&nbsp;years to be fully utilized.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At
	December&nbsp;31, 2016, we had net operating loss carryforwards in certain state jurisdictions of $516&nbsp;million before tax effect. Based on our current ability to generate
	state taxable income, it is more likely than not that the majority of these carryforwards will not be realized before they expire. Accordingly, a valuation allowance has been recorded on
	$513.7&nbsp;million of the carryforwards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	do not anticipate the expected expiration of our remaining tax holidays in Thailand and Vietnam in 2017 to have a material effect on our effective tax rate, operating results, or
	financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Unrecognized Tax Benefits
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As of December&nbsp;31, 2016, our unrecognized tax benefits totaled $89.5&nbsp;million, $71.5&nbsp;million of which, if
	recognized, would reduce our annual effective income tax rate. As of January&nbsp;2, 2016, our unrecognized tax benefits totaled $107.3&nbsp;million, $89&nbsp;million of which, if recognized,
	would reduce our annual effective income tax rate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Where
	applicable, we record potential accrued interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits from our global operations in income tax expense. As a result, we recognized tax
	benefit of $3.1&nbsp;million, tax expense of $1.3&nbsp;million, and tax benefit of $1.3&nbsp;million in the Consolidated Statements of Income in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively. We have
	accrued $22.3&nbsp;million and $26.1&nbsp;million for interest and penalties, net of tax benefit, in the Consolidated Balance Sheets at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and January&nbsp;2, 2016,
	respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A
	reconciliation of the beginning and ending amounts of unrecognized tax benefits is set forth below:
</FONT>
</P>

</EFX_BALANCE_SHEET>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	amount of income taxes we pay is subject to ongoing audits by taxing jurisdictions around the world. Our estimate of the potential outcome of any uncertain tax issue is subject to
	our assessment of the relevant risks, facts, and circumstances existing at the time. We believe that we have adequately provided for reasonably foreseeable outcomes related to these matters. However,
	our future results may include favorable or unfavorable adjustments to our estimated tax liabilities in the period the assessments are made or resolved, which may impact our effective tax rate. As of
	the date the 2016 financial statements are being issued, we and our U.S. subsidiaries have completed the Internal Revenue Service's Compliance Assurance Process Program through 2015. We also expect
	the current German tax audit for tax years 2006-2010 to be completed in 2017. We are subject to routine tax examinations in other jurisdictions. With some exceptions, we and our subsidiaries are no
	longer subject to income tax examinations by tax authorities for years prior to 2006.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;It
	is reasonably possible that, during the next 12&nbsp;months, we may realize a decrease in our uncertain tax positions, including interest and penalties, of approximately
	$16&nbsp;million, primarily as a result of audit settlements and closing tax years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
	NOTE 15. SEGMENT INFORMATION
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Segment Reporting
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We have the following reportable segments:
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Label and Graphic Materials&nbsp;&#150; manufactures and sells pressure-sensitive labeling technology and materials and films for
	graphic and reflective applications;
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Retail Branding and Information Solutions&nbsp;&#150; designs, manufactures and sells a wide variety of branding and information
	products and services, including brand and price tickets, tags and labels (including RFID inlays), and related services, supplies and equipment; and
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-9PT;'>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&#149;
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	Industrial and Healthcare
	Materials&nbsp;&#150; manufactures performance tapes, fastener solutions, and an array of pressure-sensitive
	adhesive products for various medical applications.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Intersegment
	sales are recorded at or near market prices and are eliminated in determining consolidated sales. We evaluate performance based on income from operations before interest
	expense and taxes. General corporate expenses are also excluded from the computation of income from operations for the segments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	do not disclose total assets by reportable segment since we neither generate nor review such information internally. As our reporting structure is not organized or reviewed internally
	by country, results by individual country are not provided.
</FONT>
</P>

	our Industrial and Healthcare Materials reportable segment, net sales to unaffiliated customers for the combined Performance Tapes and Vancive Medical Technologies product groups
	were $377.4&nbsp;million, $414.6&nbsp;million, and $440&nbsp;million in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</B>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Property,
	plant and equipment, net, in our U.S. and international operations was as follows:
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">
</DIV>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Software
	amortization expense from continuing operations was $37.9&nbsp;million in 2016, $37.6&nbsp;million in 2015, and $36.4&nbsp;million in 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Equity Method Investment
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In October 2016, we acquired a 22.6% interest in PragmatIC Printing Limited ("PragmatIC"), a company that develops flexible
	electronics technology. PragmatIC's primary assets are intangible assets related to its technology. We used the equity method to account for this investment. The carrying value of this investment was
	$9.5&nbsp;million as of December&nbsp;31, 2016 and was included in "Other assets" in the Consolidated Balance Sheets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Currency Effects
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Gains and losses resulting from foreign currency transactions are included in income in the period incurred. Transactions in
	foreign currencies (including receivables, payables and loans denominated in currencies other than the functional currency), including hedging impacts, decreased net income by $1.6&nbsp;million,
	$6.1&nbsp;million, and $8.7&nbsp;million in 2016, 2015, and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We
	had no operations in hyperinflationary economies in fiscal years 2016, 2015, or 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Discontinued Operations
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Loss from discontinued operations, net of tax, for 2015 included tax expense related to the completion of certain tax returns
	related to the sale of our former OCP and DES businesses. The loss from discontinued operations, net of tax, for 2014 reflected costs related to the resolution of certain post-closing adjustments in
	the third quarter of 2014. We continue to be subject to certain indemnification obligations under the terms of the purchase agreement. In addition, the tax liability associated with the sale is
	subject to the completion of tax return filings in certain foreign jurisdictions in which we operated the OCP and DES businesses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	Sale of Product Line
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In May 2015, we sold certain assets and transferred certain liabilities associated with a product line in our RBIS reportable
	segment for $1.5&nbsp;million. The pre-tax loss from the sale, when combined with exit costs related to the sale, totaled $8.5&nbsp;million. The exit costs included $3.4&nbsp;million of
	severance costs. In the first quarter of 2015, we recorded an impairment charge of approximately $2&nbsp;million related to certain long-lived assets in this product line. This loss and these costs
	were included in "Other expense, net" in the Consolidated Statements of Income.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_PAGE_EE43804_1_48">
</A>
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_BASECOLOR,"#000000" -->

<!-- TOC_END -->
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_EE43804_STATEMENT_OF_MANAGEMENT_RESPON__STA02614">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_TOC_EE43804_1">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	STATEMENT OF MANAGEMENT RESPONSIBILITY FOR FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The consolidated financial statements and accompanying information are the responsibility of and were prepared by management. The
	statements were prepared in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America and, as such, include amounts that are based on management's best estimates and
	judgments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversight
	of management's financial reporting and internal accounting control responsibilities is exercised by our Board of Directors, through its Audit and Finance Committee, which is
	comprised solely of independent directors. The Committee meets periodically with financial management, internal auditors and our independent registered public accounting firm to obtain reasonable
	assurance that each is meeting its responsibilities and to discuss matters concerning auditing, internal accounting control and financial reporting. The independent registered public accounting firm
	and our internal audit department have free access to, and periodically meet with, the Audit and Finance Committee without management present.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_EE43804_MANAGEMENT_S_REPORT_ON_INTERNA__MAN02650">
</A>
<A NAME="A2230940ZEX-13_HTM_TOC_EE43804_2">
</A>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:8.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-8.0PT;" -->
	MANAGEMENT'S REPORT ON INTERNAL CONTROL OVER FINANCIAL REPORTING
<BR>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Management is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting, as that term is
	defined in Exchange Act Rule&nbsp;13a-15(f) or 15(d)-15(f). Under the supervision and with the participation of management, including our chief executive officer and chief financial officer, we
	conducted an evaluation of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting based on
	the framework in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
	Internal Control&nbsp;&#150; Integrated Framework (2013)
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway
	Commission. Based on our evaluation under the framework in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
<I>
	Internal Control&nbsp;&#150; Integrated Framework (2013)
</I>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:9PT;">
	, management has concluded
	that internal control over financial reporting was effective as of December&nbsp;31, 2016. Management's assessment of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting as of
	December&nbsp;31, 2016 has been audited by PricewaterhouseCoopers&nbsp;LLP, an independent registered public accounting firm, as stated in their report included herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="DISPLAY:NONE;*DISPLAY:BLOCK;MARGIN-TOP:-1PT;">

	&#8203;
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_GRID,"BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID #000000 1.0PT;" -->
<FONT>
